H=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>   <font color=#939393>(8/11/00 10:58:32 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Healing</span><hr size=1> If you're a cleric and grouped with pet classes, there is a easy way to keep an eye on the pets' health. Target the creature you're killing and /assist it. It will target the pet currently getting beat on. <p><p align="left"><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="+2" color="#FF0000"><b><font size="+1">Obeah<br><a href="http://www.midnight_council.homestead.com"><img src="http://fantazone.com/mcresources/mcsig.jpg" border=0></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#242422><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub20.ezboard.com/ureog.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Reog</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>ezOP</span><br>   <font color=#939393>(8/11/00 12:15:06 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Healing</span><hr size=1> When grouped with a mage don’t start healing right after battle. Any time health is below 50% for a party member someone in the group can practice bandaging. The mage should keep the tanks supplied with bandages. The tanks and the mage should both bind wounds every chance they get. Once 50% health is reached the healers can take over. This will pay off at higher levels where some classes can bandage for more than 50%. If you have having an easy time with MOB’s you may consider not fully healing the tank. Keeping the health low allows for more practice, but be ready to chain cast healing if trouble comes. <p><P><B><FONT COLOR="#FF0000">Reog</FONT></B> the educated ogre of <A HREF="http://www.midnight_council.homestead.com"><IMG SRC = "http://www.midnight_council.homestead.com/files/mcsmall.gif" WIDTH=195 HEIGHT=32  BORDER=0></A></P>
<P><B><FONT COLOR="#FF0000">Arlo</FONT></B>/<B><FONT COLOR="#FF0000">Tinkerdo</FONT></B>
      - You spawn it, we kill it.</P>
    
    <P><B><FONT COLOR="#FF0000">Rabid</FONT></B> - lost druid from Tunare.</P></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub20.ezboard.com/uobeah.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Obeah</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>   <font color=#939393>(8/11/00 3:39:57 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Healing</span><hr size=1> Always ask the necro you group with when you should heal them. Most necros fight without full health. This way they get the full effect from their lifetap spells. <p><p align="left"><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="+2" color="#FF0000"><b><font size="+1">Obeah<br><a href="http://www.midnight_council.homestead.com"><img src="http://fantazone.com/mcresources/mcsig.jpg" border=0></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#242422><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub20.ezboard.com/usyzian.showPublicProfile?language=EN>syzian</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>   <font color=#939393>(8/11/00 3:56:45 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Healing</span><hr size=1> I agree!  Being one of those necros that doesn't worry about having full health (as long as I have 1/2 a bar) I agree with obeah.  One of the most annoying things in my oppinion are the clerics who just start healing me wether I say not to or not and then I'm full and they say oom then sit down.  Well the tanks are still not at full and we have to wait for them to med some.  I'd much rather see them have healed the tanks and let me tap a little durring battle.   Much faster, easier, and mana efficient. <p><A HREF="MAILTO:thespek@hotmail.com"><B>Syzian</A></B><BR>
